      "positive_prompt": "A richly textured forest scene, with tall trees forming a dense canopy. The forest floor is detailed with leaves, roots, and subtle texture, receding into depth between the trees. The entire scene has a handcrafted oil-painted aesthetic with strong depth and natural composition.\n\nThe scene begins completely still, like a frozen painting. The camera begins a slow, smooth pan from left to right, revealing more of the forest as it moves, maintaining a cinematic and stable motion. For most of the shot the forest remains entirely undisturbed — no movement, no life, just the still and silent woodland passing gradually through frame.\n\nNear the later portion of the pan, a hare is already in motion as it enters the frame from the left edge — mid-sprint, fully committed to its run.\n\nThe hare moves with a realistic grounded gallop: hind legs gather tightly beneath the body, then drive powerfully into the ground to propel it forward. The front legs extend to catch the body on landing, briefly absorbing impact before lifting again. Each stride has a clear sequence of compression → push-off → airborne extension → landing, with visible contact against the ground at every cycle.\n\nThere is no paddling or swimming-like motion — the limbs do not cycle continuously in the air. Instead, each stride is weight-driven and physically connected to the ground, with brief airborne moments only at the peak of each bound. The body stretches forward during extension and compresses tightly during collection, creating a rhythmic, spring-like motion.\n\nThe motion feels continuous and uninterrupted, as if the hare has been running long before the camera revealed it. It weaves naturally through the forest, passing behind and between tree trunks as the camera continues its steady pan.\n\nIt crosses the frame quickly and exits off the right edge, leaving the forest still and silent once more.\n\nThe environment remains completely static throughout, emphasizing the contrast between the stillness of the forest and the hare’s brief, fluid motion.\n\nCinematic, smooth animation with controlled pacing and strong sense of depth. No text, subtitles, captions, credits, letters, or symbols anywhere in the frame.",
